			<Question qid="0003682-1" qtype="information">Do you have information about Spine surgery - discharge</Question>
			<Answer>You were in the hospital for spine surgery. You probably had a problem with one or more disks or spine bones. A disk is a cushion that separates the bones in your spine (vertebrae). Now that you're going home, follow the surgeon's instructions on how to care for yourself while you recover.</Answer>
